{
  "info": {
    "name": "Automations - Local",
    "description": "Postman collection for managing OpenHands Cloud automations.\n\n## Setup\n1. Import both collection and environment JSON files\n2. Set OPENHANDS_API_KEY in the environment\n3. Set ISSUE_NUMBER and REPO in the environment before triggering\n\n## Workflow (Option 3: Specify Issue via Message)\n1. Set ISSUE_NUMBER (e.g., 42) and REPO (e.g., 11thandOrange/BusyBuddy_v2)\n2. POST /dispatch to trigger automation\n3. Poll GET /runs/{run_id} until status=RUNNING and conversation_id appears\n4. POST /messages with issue context\n5. GET /messages to view logs\n\n## Repositories Covered\n- 11thandOrange/BusyBuddy_v2\n- 11thandOrange/OrderMate  \n- HeyItsChloe/mates4ever (Orbit)\n- openhands/openhands",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "https://app.all-hands.dev/api"
    },
    {
      "key": "OPENHANDS_API_KEY",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "ISSUE_NUMBER",
      "value": "42",
      "description": "GitHub issue number to process"
    },
    {
      "key": "REPO",
      "value": "11thandOrange/BusyBuddy_v2",
      "description": "Repository in format owner/repo"
    }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{OPENHANDS_API_KEY}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Core Operations",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List All Automations",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/automation/v1",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "automation",
                "v1"
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Trigger Automation (Dispatch)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('run_id', jsonData.id);",
                  "console.log('Run ID:', jsonData.id);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"keep_alive\": false\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/automation/v1/:automation_id/dispatch",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "automation",
                "v1",
                ":automation_id",
                "dispatch"
              ],
              "variable": [
                {
                  "key": "automation_id",
                  "value": "{{AUTOMATION_ID}}"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Trigger automation. Save run_id from response."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Poll Run Status",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (jsonData.conversation_id) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('conversation_id', jsonData.conversation_id);",
                  "    console.log('Conversation ID:', jsonData.conversation_id);",
                  "}",
                  "console.log('Status:', jsonData.status);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/automation/v1/:automation_id/runs/:run_id",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "automation",
                "v1",
                ":automation_id",
                "runs",
                ":run_id"
              ],
              "variable": [
                {
                  "key": "automation_id",
                  "value": "{{AUTOMATION_ID}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "run_id",
                  "value": "{{run_id}}"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Poll until status=RUNNING and conversation_id appears"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Send Issue Context Message",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"role\": \"user\",\n    \"content\": \"Please process GitHub issue #{{ISSUE_NUMBER}} in repository {{REPO}}.\\n\\nFetch the issue details, implement the requested changes, create tests, and open a pull request.\\n\\nIssue URL: https://github.com/{{REPO}}/issues/{{ISSUE_NUMBER}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/conversation/:conversation_id/messages",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "conversation",
                ":conversation_id",
                "messages"
              ],
              "variable": [
                {
                  "key": "conversation_id",
                  "value": "{{conversation_id}}"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Send the issue context to the conversation. This tells the agent which issue to work on."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Conversation Messages (Logs)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/conversation/:conversation_id/messages",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "conversation",
                ":conversation_id",
                "messages"
              ],
              "variable": [
                {
                  "key": "conversation_id",
                  "value": "{{conversation_id}}"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "View all messages in the conversation (logs)"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List Automation Runs",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/automation/v1/:automation_id/runs?limit=10",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "automation",
                "v1",
                ":automation_id",
                "runs"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "limit",
                  "value": "10"
                }
              ],
              "variable": [
                {
                  "key": "automation_id",
                  "value": "{{AUTOMATION_ID}}"
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Automation Details",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/automation/v1/:automation_id",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "automation",
                "v1",
                ":automation_id"
              ],
              "variable": [
                {
                  "key": "automation_id",
                  "value": "{{AUTOMATION_ID}}"
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
